cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as machine translation and part of speech tagging, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also explores the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the use of data-driven sub-word units and word embeddings learned using a character CNN suggests the paper may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the sensitivity of the neural machine translation system to the ratio of source and target tokens, which could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
